title: Title IX training and professional development materials

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Nevada Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Current training materials used for professional development and other staff/teacher training as related to Title IX protections against sexual harassment and sexual violence. These materials may include, but do not need to be limited to, links to online resources, PowerPoint or other slideshow presentations, training manuals, lesson plans and any other printed or digital resources used to train teachers and other staff/faculty at the University of Nevada, Reno. 

Resources only available in print can be scanned digitally and delivered.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Jessica Cabrera

title: Baynard Woods Police Arrest Record (Maryland State Police)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Maryland Public Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Any record of Baynard Woods's arrest by the police for posession of marijuana between 2018 and 2024. 
Baynard Woods is a writer and journalist based in Baltimore, and author of books 'Inheritance: An Autobiography of Whiteness'and 'I Got a Monster: The Rise and Fall of America's Most Corrupt Police Squad.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Lina Chang

title: Audio recording of Eric Adams' "Whopper Summit" at New York Burger King

communications.subject: New York Freedom of Information Law Request: Audio recording of Eric Adams' "Whopper Summit" at New York Burger King
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the New York Freedom of Information Law, I hereby request the following records:

The audio recording Mayor Eric Adams' March 2024 "Whopper summit" at the 106 Fulton St. Burger King. According to media reports published soon after, "his assistant recorded the meeting with a cell phone." I am requesting a copy of that recording. https://nypost.com/2024/03/23/us-news/mayor-adams-visits-nyc-burger-king-resident-claims-is-open-air-drug-bazaar/

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Ben Welsh

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: FBI files: Leo Stanley Berry
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

I request an electronic copy of all FBI files on Leo Stanley Berry, a military veteran and member of the Black Panther Party who died in March 2024. This is his obituary: https://www.nytimes.com/2024/03/26/nyregion/lee-berry-dead.html

I request that your agency conduct a full CRS search, as well as a cross reference search, to retrieve records related to this prominent American.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Ben Welsh
